bug.author: Futrime
bug.summary: Errors when loading models from storage.googleapis.com
bug.description:
To get help from the community, we encourage using Stack Overflow and the <denchmark-link:https://stackoverflow.com/questions/tagged/tensorflow.js>tensorflow.js</denchmark-link> tag. <denchmark-h:h4>TensorFlow.js version</denchmark-h>
1.6.0 <denchmark-h:h4>Browser version</denchmark-h>
Firefox 73.0.1(64bit) <denchmark-h:h4>Describe the problem or feature request</denchmark-h>
When loading the bodypix model MobileNetV1 with stride 32, it always returns HTTP ERROR 404, regardless of quantification and multiplier. One of the error example is the URL below: https://storage.googleapis.com/tfjs-models/savedmodel/bodypix/mobilenet/float/075/model-stride32.json <denchmark-h:h4>Code to reproduce the bug / link to feature request</denchmark-h>
If you would like to get help from the community, we encourage using Stack Overflow and the <denchmark-link:https://stackoverflow.com/questions/tagged/tensorflow.js>tensorflow.js</denchmark-link> tag. GitHub issues for this repository are tracked in the <denchmark-link:https://github.com/tensorflow/tfjs/issues>tfjs union repository</denchmark-link> . Please file your issue there, following the guidance in <denchmark-link:https://github.com/tensorflow/tfjs/blob/master/ISSUE_TEMPLATE.md>that issue template</denchmark-link> .

comments.comment: I think the docs for this are wrong and stride 32 is support with Mobilenet. cc <denchmark-link:https://github.com/tylerzhu-github>@tylerzhu-github</denchmark-link>
Thx Yannick for answering this. The MobileNet backbones have been changed to have stride 16 and 8 only.
<denchmark-link:https://github.com/tylerzhu-github>@tylerzhu-github</denchmark-link> thx for responding (to this and the PR)
